    "Model Choice": "A Physics-Informed Neural Network (PINN) based on a Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) augmented with Fourier feature embeddings. Justification: PINNs seamlessly integrate the known PDE, IC, and BCs without requiring labeled spatio-temporal observation data. Fourier features are specifically chosen to overcome the spectral bias of standard MLPs, which is critical for capturing sharp concentration gradients and moving fronts typical in advection-dominated transport.",
