    "Training Strategy": "Loss function: L = λ_pde · L_pde + λ_ic · L_ic, where L_pde = (1/N_c) Σ|∂u/∂t + v∂u/∂x − D∂²u/∂x²|² over N_c collocation points sampled uniformly or via Latin hypercube in (0,L)×(0,T), and L_ic = (1/N_0) Σ|u(x,0) − f(x)|² over N_0 initial-time points. No boundary loss term is needed since periodicity is enforced by construction. Optimization: Adam optimizer (lr ≈ 1e-3) for initial convergence, followed by L-BFGS for fine-tuning. Adaptive loss weighting (e.g., learning rate annealing or NTK-based weighting) to balance PDE and IC terms. Sampling refinement: residual-based adaptive sampling to concentrate collocation points in regions of high PDE residual (e.g., steep gradients from advection). Validation metrics: (1) L2 and L∞ error against a reference solution (finite-difference or spectral solver on the periodic domain), (2) mean PDE residual on a held-out test grid, (3) conservation check — monitor ∫₀ᴸ u(x,t)dx over time (should be constant for periodic BCs with no source term).",
    "Validation Failure Risks": "1. Advection-dominated regime (high Péclet number Pe = vL/D ≫ 1): PINNs struggle with transport-dominated dynamics; sharp fronts may be smeared or exhibit phase errors. Mitigation: causal training (time-marching), curriculum learning, or Sobolev training.\n2. Long-time integration: error accumulation over extended time horizons; the network may fail to maintain periodicity or conservation properties at late times. Mitigation: decompose into shorter time windows with sequential training.\n3. Spectral bias: standard MLPs preferentially learn low-frequency components; high-wavenumber content in f(x) may be under-resolved. Mitigation: increase Fourier feature frequencies or use multi-scale feature encoding.\n4. Insufficient collocation density near steep gradients: uniform sampling may miss localized features. Mitigation: adaptive residual-based sampling.\n5. Missing parameter specification: unknown v, D, L, T, and f(x) mean the workflow must be robust across regimes; hyperparameters (network size, collocation count, loss weights) must be tuned once these are specified."
