    "Physics Constraints": "(1) PDE residual: R_pde = Δu + k²u - f must vanish in Ω. (2) Boundary condition residual: R_bc = u - g on ∂Ω (Dirichlet assumed). (3) Corner singularity structure: near each re-entrant corner i, the solution decomposes as u = Σ c_j r_i^(2j/3) sin(2jθ_i/3) + u_smooth, with the leading singular exponent α = 2/3 for a 3π/2 corner. Gradients diverge as r^(-1/3), so standard L² loss on PDE residuals will be dominated by corner neighborhoods unless properly weighted. (4) Oscillatory bulk: solution varies on scale λ = 2π/k, requiring sufficient spatial resolution to avoid aliasing and the pollution effect. (5) Energy balance: ∫_Ω |∇u|² - k²|u|² dx = boundary flux terms, providing a global integral check.",
    "Model Choice": "A single neural network augmented with physics-informed feature engineering. Architecture: MLP with 6 hidden layers × 128 neurons, using sinusoidal activations (SIREN-style) to mitigate spectral bias for high-frequency oscillations. Input features are augmented with: (a) Fourier features at multiple scales {k, 2k, k/2} to capture bulk oscillations, and (b) for each re-entrant corner i, singular basis features r_i^(2/3)·sin(2θ_i/3) and r_i^(2/3)·cos(2θ_i/3) appended to the input vector, allowing the network to learn the singular coefficient without needing to approximate a non-smooth function from smooth activations alone. This single-network approach is chosen over domain decomposition because (i) the budget of 40,000 points is tight and splitting into sub-networks would dilute capacity, (ii) the singular features explicitly encode the known corner behavior, and (iii) a single network avoids interface matching conditions that would consume additional collocation points.",
    "Training Strategy": "Point budget allocation (total 40,000): (i) Bulk collocation: 22,500 points on a quasi-uniform grid over Ω. With domain ~10λ × 10λ, this gives 150 × 150 = 22,500 points, yielding 15 points per wavelength per spatial dimension (150 pts / 10λ = 15 pts/λ), which is the minimum to resolve oscillatory solutions in PINNs without severe pollution. (ii) Corner refinement: 10,000 points distributed among N_c = 10 re-entrant corners (1,000 points per corner), sampled in annular regions r ∈ [0, 0.5λ] with radial density proportional to r^(-1/3) to concentrate points where gradients are largest and PDE residuals are hardest to satisfy. (iii) Boundary collocation: 5,000 points uniformly distributed along the staircase edges (~500 points per wavelength of boundary length). (iv) Adaptive reserve: 2,500 points allocated via residual-based adaptive refinement after initial training, targeting regions with highest |R_pde|. Loss function: L = w_pde·‖R_pde‖² + w_bc·‖R_bc‖² + w_corner·Σ_i ‖R_pde‖²_{corner_i}, with w_corner = 3×w_pde to upweight corner neighborhoods. Optimizer: Adam (lr=1e-4, 20,000 iterations) followed by L-BFGS (10,000 iterations). Curriculum: train first at k_eff = k/2 for 5,000 iterations, then increase to target k, to help the network learn the spatial structure before resolving fine oscillations.",
